This is an ongoing statistical reanalysis of the data present in the paper "Deletion of the sodium/hydrogen exchanger 6 causes low bone volume in 
adult mice", authored by Daniela Schnydera, Giuseppe Albanoa, Patrycja Kucharczyk, Silvia Dolder, Mark Siegrist, Manuel Anderegg, Ganesh Pathare, Willy Hofstetter,
Roland Barond and Daniel G. Fuster, which appeared in Bone, issue 153 (2021). Full information can be found at https://doi.org/10.1016/j.bone.2021.116178

The article was published under open access with the creative commons licence CC BY-NC-ND, and the data was taken from Graphpad Prism files that were uploaded at https://datadryad.org/stash/dataset/doi:10.5061/dryad.9w0vt4bdt - there were no licences placed upon the data itself, as the readme document available within the compressed data file explains.

Part of this reanalysis involved transferring the data from GraphPad Prism 9 files into csv files for easier analysis with R, those csv files for the relevant rscripts can be found here. 

Summary of findings:
Currently, the data associated to Figures 1A and 8A has been reanalysed, and our analysis concurs with the results presented in the paper.
